  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Eggshells, were incorporated as a binder in concrete due to their low cost and wide availability.",
    "This method takes advantage of the nutritional makeup of eggshells, which are primarily composed of calcium carbonate, magnesium carbonate, and protein, similar to lime.",
    "In Malaysia alone, around 9.47 billion eggs were consumed in 2019, translating to approximately 26 million eggs per day.",
    "The researchers aimed to repurpose eggshell waste to minimize the environmental impact of its disposal.",
    "In a study by Kamaruddin et al. [27], the potential of using eggshell powder as a partial cement replacement in Self-Compacting Concrete (SCC) was explored."
  ],
